        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sets the voltage swing level value in the DisplayPort TX that will be used during link training for a given voltage swing training level. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_dp_psu" kindref="compound">XDpPsu</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Level</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the voltage swing training level to set the DisplayPort TX level for. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TxLevel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the DisplayPort TX voltage swing level value to be used during link training.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>There are 16 possible voltage swing levels in the DisplayPort TX core that map to 4 possible voltage swing training levels in the RX device. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
